{ This push, liked by some of the worse calculating engines, forces the matters quite a bit, but doesn't seem to fully work out for Black. }
13. Bf4 { Taking on g6, as tempting as it is, only gives White a perpetual. }
13... Rf7
{ A stabilizing move. The following line is missed by some of the engines, which suggest that Black is doing very fine here, which is one of the reasons why I looked into it. }
