16. e5 Ne4 17. Be3
{ Here  17.Nxe4  Bf5  18.Nf6+  is pointless, as after  18...Qxf6  ,  the c7-pawn is no longer hanging. But now we can just reinforce our dark squares and work against the ...c5-break, which is what Black desires. }
17... Bf5 18. Nd2
{ We are challenging the e4-knight and with it, the control over the dark squares c5 and d4. }
18... c5 19. dxc5
{ Had the bishop been on a7 Black would have a smart tactic with ...Ng3! and ...d4! next, but now he also has to deal with a hanging bishop on b6. }
19... Bc7
{ Now  20.f4  allows  20...Ng3  followed by ...d4 with a mess, but instead, I propose a simple sequence leading to a small but very stable plus. }
